<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1677,2023]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[151,280,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Branchiae on segments 2–4, with distinct stalks; eyespots absent; lateral lappets on segment 3; ventral shields from segment 2; nephridial papillae may be present from segments 3–10; 17–39 pairs of notopodia from segment 4, chaetae distally serrated; neuropodia from segment 5, uncini avicular in single rows from segments 5–10; thereafter in double rows, arranged face to face, up to end of the thorax, then again in single rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1677,2023]" lastBlockId="41.[151,1436,152,538]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[198,310,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks:</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[599,724,1877,1902]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Halosphaeriaceae" genus="Amphitrite" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[599,724,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Amphitrite</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the only difference being the presence of stalked branchiae in the former. Thus, since this is the only difference, these two genera need to be revised together (
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[159,481,1957,1983]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref62479" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1988) The Amphitritinae (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 40, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="1988">Hutchings &amp; Glasby, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Nine species are valid (
<bibRefCitation author="Holthe, T." box="[780,956,1957,1983]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref62170" refString="Holthe, T. (1986 b) Evolution, Systematics, and Distribution of the Polychaeta Terebellomorpha, with a catalogue of the taxa and a bibliography. Gunneria, 55, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1986">Holthe, 1986b</bibRefCitation>
). A tenth species was recently described from the Grand 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[341,461,1997,2023]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="40" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F." box="[478,936,1997,2023]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref63133" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F. (2005) Terebellidae (Polychaeta) from the Mexican Caribbean with description of four new species. Zootaxa, 1057, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">Londoño-Mesa &amp; Carrera-Parra, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). This is the only species described in this region, although 
<taxonomicName authority="(Malmgren, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Malmgren" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[353,687,152,178]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Halosphaeriaceae" genus="Amphitrite" kingdom="Fungi" order="Microascales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[353,462,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">N. affinis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Malmgren, A. J." box="[479,679,152,178]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="355 - 410" refId="ref63208" refString="Malmgren, A. J. (1866) Nordiska Hafs-Annulater. Ofversigt af Kongl. Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm, 5, 355 - 410." type="journal article" year="1866">Malmgren, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
described from Spitsbergen, Artic Ocean, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Quatrefages, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="de Quatrefages" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Neoamphitrite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[1248,1389,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">N. edwardsi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="de Quatrefages, A." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refId="ref61056" refString="de Quatrefages, A. (1865) Histoire naturelle des Anneles marines et d'eau douce. Annelides et Gephyriens. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 58 pp. (Published in 1866)." type="book" year="1865">de Quatrefages, 1865</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from St. Vaast, 
<collectingCountry box="[574,657,192,218]" name="France" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">France</collectingCountry>
, have been also reported (
<bibRefCitation author="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I." box="[963,1222,192,218]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="11 - 50" refId="ref64128" refString="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I. (1996) Lista de especies y bibliografia de poliquetos (Polychaeta) del Gran Caribe. Anales del Instituto de Biologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Serie Zoologia, 67, 11 - 50." type="journal article" year="1996">Salazar-Vallejo, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). The main differences between species in the genus are the number of pairs of nephridial papillae, the number of lateral lappets, and the number of pairs of notopodia. Eight species have been described from subtropical waters (North Europe and North Pacific Ocean), and only three from tropical waters (Malay Archipelago and 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1315,1435,312,338]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="41" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
Sea). Nevertheless, the difference between the two tropical species is that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Caullery, 1944)" baseAuthorityName="Caullery" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[1034,1366,352,378]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Neoamphitrite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sibogae">
<emphasis box="[1034,1161,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">N. sibogae</emphasis>
(Caullery, 1944)
</taxonomicName>
, from the Malay Archipelago, was described from deep water (
<quantity box="[813,885,392,418]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.38" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="538.0">538m</quantity>
), like those from non-tropical waters which are also found in deep water, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Londono-Mesa &amp; Carrera-Parra, 2005" authorityName="Londono-Mesa &amp; Carrera-Parra" authorityYear="2005" box="[544,1138,432,458]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Neoamphitrite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="glasbyi">
<emphasis box="[544,666,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">N. glasbyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F." box="[677,1138,432,458]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref63133" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F. (2005) Terebellidae (Polychaeta) from the Mexican Caribbean with description of four new species. Zootaxa, 1057, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">Londoño-Mesa &amp; Carrera-Parra, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[264,384,472,498]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="41" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
in shallow water (
<quantity box="[615,717,472,498]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="41.0" valueMax="59.0" valueMin="23.0">23–59m</quantity>
). Other species from shallow waters in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1250,1370,472,498]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="41" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
have been reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kritzler, H." box="[355,536,512,538]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="53 - 124" refId="ref62802" refString="Kritzler, H. (1984) Chapter 52. Family Terebellidae Grube 1950. In: Uebelacker, J. M. &amp; Johnson, P. G., (Ed.), Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates Inc., Mobile, Alabama, 53 - 124." type="book chapter" year="1984">Kritzler (1984)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Quatrefages" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[547,687,512,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Neoamphitrite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[547,687,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">N. edwardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[703,805,512,538]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="29.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="29.0">29–30m</quantity>
), and 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1117,512,538]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Neoamphitrite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis box="[875,1044,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Neoamphitrite</emphasis>
sp. A
</taxonomicName>
. (
<quantity box="[1137,1194,512,538]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="12.0">12m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
